		<title>11Selling at the Market.</title>
		<content>   The auctioneer Mr.Roger Blakeway has
 the longest family connection with the
 firm.                                 
   We were told that the once popular  
 horse sales are to be phased out as   
 they are uneconomic to run.           
   Selling at Craven Arms market takes 
 place on Wednesays and Fridays.Roughly
 300-500 sheep may be sold on these    
 days,1500-2000 on a busy day.Up to 60 
 cattle may be sold this rising to as  
 many as 200 on a busy day.            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
